[2026-03-17T14:13:27Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017VabKsZazX3qUX4MNuKJ4r","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report with all the findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution Package Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/workspace/internal/evolution/` directory and related packages. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **orchestrator.go** - Full Pipeline Orchestrator (248 lines)\n\n**Purpose**: Wires all evolution stages together and executes the complete pipeline.\n\n**Key Types**:\n- `OrchestratorConfig`: Configuration struct with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir`: Root project directory\n  - `WorkflowName`: Name of the workflow to evolve\n  - `LLM`: LLMClient implementation\n  - `MinConfidence`: Filter threshold (\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\")\n  - `MaxPromptBullets`: Knowledge base pruning limit\n\n- `Orchestrator`: Main coordinator struct holding:\n  - `collector`, `classifier`, `reflector`, `curator`, `scriptGen`, `mutator`, `audit`\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `NewOrchestrator(cfg OrchestratorConfig) *Orchestrator`: Constructor\n- `Run(ctx context.Context, triggerRunID string, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*EvolutionResult, error)`: Executes full pipeline:\n  1. Stage 1: Collect data via Collector\n  2. Stage 2: Classify the run\n  3. Stage 3: Reflect to extract lessons\n  4. Stage 4: Branch on lesson category (prompt_improvement or new_step)\n  5. Stage 5: Update knowledge base and audit log\n  \n- `handleNewStep(ctx context.Context, data *CollectedData, lesson *Lesson, result *EvolutionResult) error`: Generates scripts and adds workflow steps\n\n**Special Handling**:\n- Deduplicates lessons already in knowledge base\n- Filters out lessons matching current prompt content\n- Validates workflow after modifications\n- Snapshots files before changes\n- Rolls back invalid workflow modifications\n\n---\n\n### 2. **types.go** - Core Data Structures (56 lines)\n\n**LLMClient Interface**:\n```go\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CollectedData** - Input to Classifier/Reflector:\n- `Runs`: []*domain.Run\n- `Captures`: map[string][]*domain.StepExecution (run_id → executions)\n- `KnowledgeBase`: string (JSONL contents)\n- `CurrentPrompts`: map[string]string (path → content)\n- `CurrentWorkflow`: string (.cloche file content)\n- `WorkflowPath`: string (absolute path)\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: strings\n\n**Lesson** - Extracted insight with JSON marshaling:\n- `ID`: Unique identifier (e.g., \"lesson-YYYYMMDD-NNN\")\n- `Category`: \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n- `StepType`: \"script\" or \"agent\" (for new_step)\n- `Target`: Prompt file path to update\n- `Insight`: What pattern was observed\n- `SuggestedAction`: Concrete change to make\n- `Evidence`: []string (run IDs supporting lesson)\n- `Confidence`: \"high\", \"medium\", or \"low\"\n\n**EvolutionResult** - Pipeline output:\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`, `Timestamp`\n- `Classification`: bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore\n- `Changes`: []Change (modifications made)\n- `KnowledgeDelta`: Summary of knowledge updates\n\n**Change** - Individual modification:\n- `Type`: \"prompt_update\", \"add_step\", \"add_script\", \"prompt_update_rollback\"\n- `File`: Relative path to modified file\n- `Reason`: Why change was made\n- `Snapshot`: Snapshot filename for rollback\n\n---\n\n### 3. **collector.go** - Data Collection (91 lines)\n\n**Collector Struct**:\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: Configuration\n\n**Collect() Method**:\nGathers all input data in this order:\n1. Knowledge base from `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/{workflow}.jsonl`\n2. Workflow file from `.cloche/{workflow}.cloche`\n3. Prompt files (extracted via regex from workflow)\n4. Runs from EvolutionStore (since last evolution)\n5. Step executions from CaptureStore for each run\n\n**Helper**:\n- `extractPromptFiles(workflow string) []string`: Uses regex to find `file(\"path\")` references\n\n---\n\n### 4. **curator.go** - Prompt Updating (194 lines)\n\n**Curator Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient for merging\n- `Audit`: AuditLogger for snapshots\n\n**Apply() Method**:\nMerges a lesson into a prompt file using ACE (Agentic Context Engineering):\n1. Guards against duplicate lessons (case-insensitive substring match)\n2. Calls LLM to merge lesson into prompt\n3. Strips code fences from LLM response\n4. Validates response isn't conversational meta-text\n5. Falls back to direct append if LLM returns conversational text\n6. Creates snapshot before writing\n7. Validates written content with sanity check\n8. Rolls back to snapshot if content fails sanity check\n\n**Key Helpers**:\n- `lessonAlreadyPresent(currentPrompt string, lesson *Lesson) bool`: Substring matching\n- `isConversationalResponse(s string) bool`: Detects meta-conversation (regex pattern matching)\n- `stripCodeFences(s string) string`: Removes markdown fences\n- `appendLessonDirectly(current string, lesson *Lesson) string`: Fallback append\n- `promptSanityCheck(content string) bool`: Validates output (not empty, has heading, not conversational)\n\n**Corruption Protection**:\n- Detects when LLM returns conversational text without code fences\n- Detects empty responses\n- Detects responses lacking markdown structure\n- Rolls back to snapshot in all cases\n\n---\n\n### 5. **classifier.go** - Run Classification (50 lines)\n\n**Classifier Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient\n\n**Classify() Method**:\nCategorizes a run prompt into one category:\n- `bug`: Fixing defects/vulnerabilities/regressions\n- `feedback`: Code review issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture, style)\n- `feature`: New functionality\n- `enhancement`: Improving existing functionality\n- `chore`: Maintenance, dependencies, CI\n\nDefaults to \"feature\" on parse error.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **reflector.go** - Lesson Extraction (129 lines)\n\n**Reflector Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient\n- `MinConfidence`: \"low\", \"medium\", or \"high\" filter\n\n**Reflect() Method**:\nAnalyzes execution history and extracts lessons:\n1. Builds comprehensive user prompt with classification, knowledge base, workflow, prompts, run history\n2. Calls LLM to extract structured lessons\n3. Filters by minimum confidence level\n4. Deduplicates against knowledge base (filters out lessons already recorded)\n\n**Confidence Levels**:\n- `high` (3): 4+ occurrences or clear pattern\n- `medium` (2): 2-3 occurrences\n- `low` (1): 1 occurrence or ambiguous\n- Default (0): Other\n\n---\n\n### 7. **scriptgen.go** - Script Generation (113 lines)\n\n**ScriptGenerator Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient for code generation\n\n**Generate() Method**:\nCreates a new shell script via LLM:\n1. Calls LLM to generate script with path and content\n2. Validates path doesn't contain \"..\"\n3. Validates path starts with \"scripts/\" or \".cloche/scripts/\"\n4. Validates content starts with shebang (#!)\n5. Verifies path doesn't escape project directory\n6. Checks script doesn't already exist (no overwrites)\n7. Creates parent directories\n8. Writes file non-executable (0644)\n\n**Validation**:\n- `validateScriptPath(p string) error`: Path safety checks\n\n**GeneratedScript** return type:\n- `Path`: Relative path to created script\n- `Content`: Script body\n\n---\n\n### 8. **audit.go** - Auditing & Knowledge Base (173 lines)\n\n**AuditLogger Struct**:\n- `ProjectDir`: Root directory\n- `MaxPromptBullets`: Pruning limit (0 = unlimited)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n\n- `Log(result *EvolutionResult) error`: Appends to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` (one JSON per line)\n\n- `Snapshot(relativePath string) (string, error)`: Copies file to `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/{timestamp-basename}`\n\n- `Restore(relativePath string, snapName string) error`: Restores from snapshot\n\n- `KnowledgePath(workflowName string) string`: Returns `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/{workflow}.jsonl` path\n\n- `UpdateKnowledge(workflowName string, lessons []Lesson) error`: \n  - Reads existing JSONL knowledge base\n  - Merges lessons (updates by ID, appends new)\n  - Prunes to MaxPromptBullets if set (keeps most recent N)\n  - Writes back as JSONL\n\n**Helpers**:\n- `readKnowledge(path string) ([]Lesson, error)`: Parses JSONL\n- `writeKnowledge(path string, lessons []Lesson) error`: Writes JSONL\n\n---\n\n### 9. **trigger.go** - Debounced Evolution Triggering (63 lines)\n\n**TriggerConfig**:\n- `DebounceSeconds`: int (default 30)\n- `RunFunc`: Callback function when timer fires\n\n**Trigger Struct**:\n- Maintains per-project+workflow debounce timers\n- Thread-safe (sync.Mutex)\n\n**Methods**:\n- `NewTrigger(cfg TriggerConfig) *Trigger`: Creates trigger\n- `Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID string)`: Schedules evolution run, resets timer if pending, uses latest runID\n- `Stop()`: Cancels all pending timers\n\n**Behavior**: Debounces rapid calls for the same project+workflow combo, fires once with latest runID\n\n---\n\n### 10. **llmclient.go** - LLM Command Wrapper (58 lines)\n\n**CommandLLMClient Struct**:\n- `Command`: Executable name (e.g., \"claude\")\n- `Args`: Extra arguments\n\n**Complete() Method**:\nInvokes LLM via shell command:\n1. Makes copy of Args (doesn't mutate original)\n2. Appends `-p` (print mode for non-interactive output)\n3. Appends `--system-prompt {systemPrompt}` if non-empty\n4. Appends `--output-format text`\n5. Passes user prompt via stdin\n6. Strips CLAUDECODE env var to prevent conflicts\n7. Captures and returns stdout (trimmed)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **ports/store.go** - Evolution-Related Interfaces (59 lines)\n\n**EvolutionStore Interface**:\n```go\nSaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\nGetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\nListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**EvolutionEntry Struct**:\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`\n- `CreatedAt`: time.Time\n- `Classification`: bug/feature/etc\n- `ChangesJSON`, `KnowledgeDelta`: strings\n\n**Related Stores**:\n- `CaptureStore`: Persists step execution captures\n- `LogStore`: Persists log file entries\n- `RunStore`: Persists run metadata\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Test Coverage** (2,158 test lines across 3 files)\n\n**evolution_test.go** (1,198 lines): Core unit tests\n- Collector, Classifier, Reflector, AuditLogger\n- Curator (prompt updates, code fence stripping, conversational rejection, rollbacks)\n- ScriptGenerator (validation, path safety)\n- CommandLLMClient (print mode, system prompt handling, arg preservation)\n- Orchestrator (end-to-end, new steps, deduplication, validation)\n- Content-change guards (lesson deduplication)\n- Integration tests (multiple cycles, store interactions)\n\n**corruption_test.go** (960 lines): Corruption & edge case tests\n- Curator corruption scenarios (conversational text, short responses, empty responses)\n- Rollback validation and snapshot preservation\n- Race condition tests (concurrent Apply calls)\n- Prompt sanity check validation\n- Orchestrator edge cases (duplicate lessons, workflow cycles)\n\n**scriptgen_test.go** (128 lines): Script generation safety\n- Path traversal prevention\n- Path containment validation\n- Shebang requirement\n- No-overwrite protection\n- Valid path acceptance\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Architecture Summary**\n\n**Hexagonal Pattern**:\n- Domain: Lesson, CollectedData, EvolutionResult, Change\n- Ports: LLMClient, EvolutionStore, CaptureStore\n- Adapters: CommandLLMClient, Curator, Classifier, Reflector, ScriptGenerator\n\n**Data Flow**:\n```\nTrigger.Fire()\n    ↓\nOrchestrator.Run()\n    ├─ Collector.Collect() → CollectedData\n    ├─ Classifier.Classify() → classification string\n    ├─ Reflector.Reflect() → []Lesson\n    ├─ Curator.Apply() / handleNewStep()\n    │   ├─ AuditLogger.Snapshot()\n    │   ├─ LLM modifications\n    │   ├─ Validation & rollback\n    │   └─ AuditLogger.Snapshot()/Restore()\n    └─ AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() → JSONL KB\n```\n\n**Safety Mechanisms**:\n- Snapshot-based rollback on validation failures\n- Lesson deduplication against knowledge base\n- Sanity checks on LLM output (conversational detection)\n- Script path validation (traversal prevention)\n- Duplicate step prevention in workflow\n- Workflow validation after mutations\n- File existence checks before overwrites\n\n---\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll relevant files:\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` (1,198 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go` (960 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go` (128 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger_test.go` (89 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a25e7044e38731a33 (use SendMessage with to: 'a25e7044e38731a33' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 73257\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 52641</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7e0d0a9-9907-4df1-a980-7e0c554bc17f","uuid":"95942a0e-13b4-4667-9150-5e7688e8d6aa","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:08:20.661Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the internal/evolution/ directory. I need to understand:\n1. The orchestrator.go file - its full contents\n2. The population package/types - Population, AddCandidate, Promote methods\n3. The curator package/types - Curate method\n4. Any existing types like EvaluateRun, fitness evaluation\n5. The ports/interfaces related to evolution\n6. Any existing tests in the evolution package\n\nRead ALL files in internal/evolution/ and any related packages. Also check internal/ports/ for evolution-related interfaces.","agentId":"a25e7044e38731a33","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary report with all the findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Evolution Package Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `/workspace/internal/evolution/` directory and related packages. Here's a complete breakdown:\n\n### 1. **orchestrator.go** - Full Pipeline Orchestrator (248 lines)\n\n**Purpose**: Wires all evolution stages together and executes the complete pipeline.\n\n**Key Types**:\n- `OrchestratorConfig`: Configuration struct with fields:\n  - `ProjectDir`: Root project directory\n  - `WorkflowName`: Name of the workflow to evolve\n  - `LLM`: LLMClient implementation\n  - `MinConfidence`: Filter threshold (\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\")\n  - `MaxPromptBullets`: Knowledge base pruning limit\n\n- `Orchestrator`: Main coordinator struct holding:\n  - `collector`, `classifier`, `reflector`, `curator`, `scriptGen`, `mutator`, `audit`\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `NewOrchestrator(cfg OrchestratorConfig) *Orchestrator`: Constructor\n- `Run(ctx context.Context, triggerRunID string, evoStore ports.EvolutionStore, capStore ports.CaptureStore) (*EvolutionResult, error)`: Executes full pipeline:\n  1. Stage 1: Collect data via Collector\n  2. Stage 2: Classify the run\n  3. Stage 3: Reflect to extract lessons\n  4. Stage 4: Branch on lesson category (prompt_improvement or new_step)\n  5. Stage 5: Update knowledge base and audit log\n  \n- `handleNewStep(ctx context.Context, data *CollectedData, lesson *Lesson, result *EvolutionResult) error`: Generates scripts and adds workflow steps\n\n**Special Handling**:\n- Deduplicates lessons already in knowledge base\n- Filters out lessons matching current prompt content\n- Validates workflow after modifications\n- Snapshots files before changes\n- Rolls back invalid workflow modifications\n\n---\n\n### 2. **types.go** - Core Data Structures (56 lines)\n\n**LLMClient Interface**:\n```go\ntype LLMClient interface {\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, systemPrompt, userPrompt string) (string, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CollectedData** - Input to Classifier/Reflector:\n- `Runs`: []*domain.Run\n- `Captures`: map[string][]*domain.StepExecution (run_id → executions)\n- `KnowledgeBase`: string (JSONL contents)\n- `CurrentPrompts`: map[string]string (path → content)\n- `CurrentWorkflow`: string (.cloche file content)\n- `WorkflowPath`: string (absolute path)\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: strings\n\n**Lesson** - Extracted insight with JSON marshaling:\n- `ID`: Unique identifier (e.g., \"lesson-YYYYMMDD-NNN\")\n- `Category`: \"prompt_improvement\" or \"new_step\"\n- `StepType`: \"script\" or \"agent\" (for new_step)\n- `Target`: Prompt file path to update\n- `Insight`: What pattern was observed\n- `SuggestedAction`: Concrete change to make\n- `Evidence`: []string (run IDs supporting lesson)\n- `Confidence`: \"high\", \"medium\", or \"low\"\n\n**EvolutionResult** - Pipeline output:\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`, `Timestamp`\n- `Classification`: bug/feedback/feature/enhancement/chore\n- `Changes`: []Change (modifications made)\n- `KnowledgeDelta`: Summary of knowledge updates\n\n**Change** - Individual modification:\n- `Type`: \"prompt_update\", \"add_step\", \"add_script\", \"prompt_update_rollback\"\n- `File`: Relative path to modified file\n- `Reason`: Why change was made\n- `Snapshot`: Snapshot filename for rollback\n\n---\n\n### 3. **collector.go** - Data Collection (91 lines)\n\n**Collector Struct**:\n- `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`: Configuration\n\n**Collect() Method**:\nGathers all input data in this order:\n1. Knowledge base from `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/{workflow}.jsonl`\n2. Workflow file from `.cloche/{workflow}.cloche`\n3. Prompt files (extracted via regex from workflow)\n4. Runs from EvolutionStore (since last evolution)\n5. Step executions from CaptureStore for each run\n\n**Helper**:\n- `extractPromptFiles(workflow string) []string`: Uses regex to find `file(\"path\")` references\n\n---\n\n### 4. **curator.go** - Prompt Updating (194 lines)\n\n**Curator Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient for merging\n- `Audit`: AuditLogger for snapshots\n\n**Apply() Method**:\nMerges a lesson into a prompt file using ACE (Agentic Context Engineering):\n1. Guards against duplicate lessons (case-insensitive substring match)\n2. Calls LLM to merge lesson into prompt\n3. Strips code fences from LLM response\n4. Validates response isn't conversational meta-text\n5. Falls back to direct append if LLM returns conversational text\n6. Creates snapshot before writing\n7. Validates written content with sanity check\n8. Rolls back to snapshot if content fails sanity check\n\n**Key Helpers**:\n- `lessonAlreadyPresent(currentPrompt string, lesson *Lesson) bool`: Substring matching\n- `isConversationalResponse(s string) bool`: Detects meta-conversation (regex pattern matching)\n- `stripCodeFences(s string) string`: Removes markdown fences\n- `appendLessonDirectly(current string, lesson *Lesson) string`: Fallback append\n- `promptSanityCheck(content string) bool`: Validates output (not empty, has heading, not conversational)\n\n**Corruption Protection**:\n- Detects when LLM returns conversational text without code fences\n- Detects empty responses\n- Detects responses lacking markdown structure\n- Rolls back to snapshot in all cases\n\n---\n\n### 5. **classifier.go** - Run Classification (50 lines)\n\n**Classifier Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient\n\n**Classify() Method**:\nCategorizes a run prompt into one category:\n- `bug`: Fixing defects/vulnerabilities/regressions\n- `feedback`: Code review issues (DRY, SOLID, architecture, style)\n- `feature`: New functionality\n- `enhancement`: Improving existing functionality\n- `chore`: Maintenance, dependencies, CI\n\nDefaults to \"feature\" on parse error.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **reflector.go** - Lesson Extraction (129 lines)\n\n**Reflector Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient\n- `MinConfidence`: \"low\", \"medium\", or \"high\" filter\n\n**Reflect() Method**:\nAnalyzes execution history and extracts lessons:\n1. Builds comprehensive user prompt with classification, knowledge base, workflow, prompts, run history\n2. Calls LLM to extract structured lessons\n3. Filters by minimum confidence level\n4. Deduplicates against knowledge base (filters out lessons already recorded)\n\n**Confidence Levels**:\n- `high` (3): 4+ occurrences or clear pattern\n- `medium` (2): 2-3 occurrences\n- `low` (1): 1 occurrence or ambiguous\n- Default (0): Other\n\n---\n\n### 7. **scriptgen.go** - Script Generation (113 lines)\n\n**ScriptGenerator Struct**:\n- `LLM`: LLMClient for code generation\n\n**Generate() Method**:\nCreates a new shell script via LLM:\n1. Calls LLM to generate script with path and content\n2. Validates path doesn't contain \"..\"\n3. Validates path starts with \"scripts/\" or \".cloche/scripts/\"\n4. Validates content starts with shebang (#!)\n5. Verifies path doesn't escape project directory\n6. Checks script doesn't already exist (no overwrites)\n7. Creates parent directories\n8. Writes file non-executable (0644)\n\n**Validation**:\n- `validateScriptPath(p string) error`: Path safety checks\n\n**GeneratedScript** return type:\n- `Path`: Relative path to created script\n- `Content`: Script body\n\n---\n\n### 8. **audit.go** - Auditing & Knowledge Base (173 lines)\n\n**AuditLogger Struct**:\n- `ProjectDir`: Root directory\n- `MaxPromptBullets`: Pruning limit (0 = unlimited)\n\n**Key Methods**:\n\n- `Log(result *EvolutionResult) error`: Appends to `.cloche/evolution/log.jsonl` (one JSON per line)\n\n- `Snapshot(relativePath string) (string, error)`: Copies file to `.cloche/evolution/snapshots/{timestamp-basename}`\n\n- `Restore(relativePath string, snapName string) error`: Restores from snapshot\n\n- `KnowledgePath(workflowName string) string`: Returns `.cloche/evolution/knowledge/{workflow}.jsonl` path\n\n- `UpdateKnowledge(workflowName string, lessons []Lesson) error`: \n  - Reads existing JSONL knowledge base\n  - Merges lessons (updates by ID, appends new)\n  - Prunes to MaxPromptBullets if set (keeps most recent N)\n  - Writes back as JSONL\n\n**Helpers**:\n- `readKnowledge(path string) ([]Lesson, error)`: Parses JSONL\n- `writeKnowledge(path string, lessons []Lesson) error`: Writes JSONL\n\n---\n\n### 9. **trigger.go** - Debounced Evolution Triggering (63 lines)\n\n**TriggerConfig**:\n- `DebounceSeconds`: int (default 30)\n- `RunFunc`: Callback function when timer fires\n\n**Trigger Struct**:\n- Maintains per-project+workflow debounce timers\n- Thread-safe (sync.Mutex)\n\n**Methods**:\n- `NewTrigger(cfg TriggerConfig) *Trigger`: Creates trigger\n- `Fire(projectDir, workflowName, runID string)`: Schedules evolution run, resets timer if pending, uses latest runID\n- `Stop()`: Cancels all pending timers\n\n**Behavior**: Debounces rapid calls for the same project+workflow combo, fires once with latest runID\n\n---\n\n### 10. **llmclient.go** - LLM Command Wrapper (58 lines)\n\n**CommandLLMClient Struct**:\n- `Command`: Executable name (e.g., \"claude\")\n- `Args`: Extra arguments\n\n**Complete() Method**:\nInvokes LLM via shell command:\n1. Makes copy of Args (doesn't mutate original)\n2. Appends `-p` (print mode for non-interactive output)\n3. Appends `--system-prompt {systemPrompt}` if non-empty\n4. Appends `--output-format text`\n5. Passes user prompt via stdin\n6. Strips CLAUDECODE env var to prevent conflicts\n7. Captures and returns stdout (trimmed)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **ports/store.go** - Evolution-Related Interfaces (59 lines)\n\n**EvolutionStore Interface**:\n```go\nSaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\nGetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\nListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**EvolutionEntry Struct**:\n- `ID`, `ProjectDir`, `WorkflowName`, `TriggerRunID`\n- `CreatedAt`: time.Time\n- `Classification`: bug/feature/etc\n- `ChangesJSON`, `KnowledgeDelta`: strings\n\n**Related Stores**:\n- `CaptureStore`: Persists step execution captures\n- `LogStore`: Persists log file entries\n- `RunStore`: Persists run metadata\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Test Coverage** (2,158 test lines across 3 files)\n\n**evolution_test.go** (1,198 lines): Core unit tests\n- Collector, Classifier, Reflector, AuditLogger\n- Curator (prompt updates, code fence stripping, conversational rejection, rollbacks)\n- ScriptGenerator (validation, path safety)\n- CommandLLMClient (print mode, system prompt handling, arg preservation)\n- Orchestrator (end-to-end, new steps, deduplication, validation)\n- Content-change guards (lesson deduplication)\n- Integration tests (multiple cycles, store interactions)\n\n**corruption_test.go** (960 lines): Corruption & edge case tests\n- Curator corruption scenarios (conversational text, short responses, empty responses)\n- Rollback validation and snapshot preservation\n- Race condition tests (concurrent Apply calls)\n- Prompt sanity check validation\n- Orchestrator edge cases (duplicate lessons, workflow cycles)\n\n**scriptgen_test.go** (128 lines): Script generation safety\n- Path traversal prevention\n- Path containment validation\n- Shebang requirement\n- No-overwrite protection\n- Valid path acceptance\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Architecture Summary**\n\n**Hexagonal Pattern**:\n- Domain: Lesson, CollectedData, EvolutionResult, Change\n- Ports: LLMClient, EvolutionStore, CaptureStore\n- Adapters: CommandLLMClient, Curator, Classifier, Reflector, ScriptGenerator\n\n**Data Flow**:\n```\nTrigger.Fire()\n    ↓\nOrchestrator.Run()\n    ├─ Collector.Collect() → CollectedData\n    ├─ Classifier.Classify() → classification string\n    ├─ Reflector.Reflect() → []Lesson\n    ├─ Curator.Apply() / handleNewStep()\n    │   ├─ AuditLogger.Snapshot()\n    │   ├─ LLM modifications\n    │   ├─ Validation & rollback\n    │   └─ AuditLogger.Snapshot()/Restore()\n    └─ AuditLogger.UpdateKnowledge() → JSONL KB\n```\n\n**Safety Mechanisms**:\n- Snapshot-based rollback on validation failures\n- Lesson deduplication against knowledge base\n- Sanity checks on LLM output (conversational detection)\n- Script path validation (traversal prevention)\n- Duplicate step prevention in workflow\n- Workflow validation after mutations\n- File existence checks before overwrites\n\n---\n\n### File Paths\n\nAll relevant files:\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/orchestrator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/types.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/collector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/curator.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/classifier.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/reflector.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/audit.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/llmclient.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/evolution_test.go` (1,198 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/corruption_test.go` (960 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/scriptgen_test.go` (128 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/trigger_test.go` (89 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":52641,"totalTokens":73257,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":974,"cache_read_input_tokens":68446,"output_tokens":3830,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":974},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
