[2026-03-17T14:13:27Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011hfDmo89C3udi3vGcWKPt1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have gathered comprehensive information about the evolution system. Let me create a final summary report.\n\n## Summary: Population-Related Files in /workspace\n\nBased on my thorough search of the /workspace project, **there are NO files related to \"population\" in the traditional sense** (as in population-based optimization, genetic algorithms, or Pareto selection). However, I found an extensive **Self-Evolution System** that appears to be what you're looking for. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### Key Finding\n\nThe search for \"Population\", \"AddCandidate\", \"Promote\", \"Pareto\", \"fitness\", and \"EvaluateRun\" yielded no results. This indicates that the codebase does not implement population-based evolutionary algorithms. Instead, it implements a **self-improving system based on lessons and reflection**.\n\n### Evolution System Architecture\n\nThe Cloche project implements a sophisticated **self-evolution pipeline** designed to automatically improve workflows and prompts:\n\n**Files in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`:**\n\n1. **types.go** - Core data structures:\n   - `LLMClient` interface\n   - `CollectedData` - input to pipeline\n   - `Lesson` - structured insights with ID, category, insight, suggested_action, evidence, confidence\n   - `EvolutionResult` - pipeline output\n   - `Change` - tracks file modifications\n\n2. **orchestrator.go** - Main pipeline coordinator:\n   - Wires all stages together: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor branches\n   - Handles lesson deduplication\n   - Routes lessons by category to appropriate executors\n   - Saves evolution results to store\n\n3. **collector.go** - Gathers workflow data:\n   - Collects runs, step executions, knowledge base, prompts, workflow file\n   - Scoped by project_dir + workflow_name\n\n4. **classifier.go** - LLM-based run categorization:\n   - Classifies runs as: bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, or chore\n\n5. **reflector.go** - LLM-based lesson extraction:\n   - Analyzes execution history and traces\n   - Produces structured lessons with evidence and confidence levels\n   - Filters by minimum confidence (low/medium/high)\n   - Deduplicates against knowledge base\n\n6. **curator.go** - Prompt evolution via ACE principles:\n   - Merges lessons into prompt files as structured bullets\n   - Guards against LLM conversational responses\n   - Post-write sanity checks with rollback capability\n   - Snapshot-based recovery\n\n7. **scriptgen.go** - Generates validation scripts:\n   - LLM-based script generation for new validation steps\n   - Path validation (scripts/ or .cloche/scripts/)\n   - Shebang line verification\n\n8. **trigger.go** - Evolution trigger mechanism:\n   - Debounces evolution runs per project+workflow\n   - Prevents duplicate analysis of rapid runs\n\n9. **audit.go** - Audit logging and state management:\n   - Records evolution passes as JSONL\n   - Manages snapshots for rollback\n   - Updates knowledge base with deduplication and pruning\n   - Supports MaxPromptBullets limit\n\n10. **llmclient.go** - CommandLLMClient implementation:\n    - Invokes external LLM via shell command\n    - Uses print mode (-p) for structured output\n    - Passes system prompt separately\n\n**Test files:**\n- `evolution_test.go` - Main evolution tests\n- `corruption_test.go` - Curator robustness tests (LLM output corruption scenarios)\n- `scriptgen_test.go` - Script generation tests\n- `trigger_test.go` - Debounce mechanism tests\n\n### Key Differences from Population-Based Evolution\n\nThis system uses:\n- **Structured lessons** (not candidate solutions)\n- **Confidence scoring** (high/medium/low, not fitness scores)\n- **ID-based deduplication** (not Pareto dominance)\n- **Lesson categories** (prompt_improvement, new_step - not genetic operators)\n- **Single best path** (not population selection)\n\n### Related Interfaces (in `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n```go\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Design Documentation\n\n- **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`** - Complete architectural design\n- **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`** - Implementation tasks and plan\n\nThis is a **lesson-based evolution system**, not a population-based optimization system. It evolves workflows through accumulated knowledge from run history rather than maintaining candidate populations."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af9e0cb022beff019 (use SendMessage with to: 'af9e0cb022beff019' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 70247\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 50825</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f7e0d0a9-9907-4df1-a980-7e0c554bc17f","uuid":"fcd340f3-c9ec-44e3-94ba-c55392acca94","timestamp":"2026-03-17T14:09:23.040Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read ALL files related to \"population\" in the /workspace project. Search for:\n1. Any files in internal/evolution/ that mention \"population\" \n2. Any population package or types\n3. Search for \"Population\", \"AddCandidate\", \"Promote\", \"Pareto\", \"fitness\", \"EvaluateRun\" across the entire codebase\n\nRead the full contents of any matching files.","agentId":"af9e0cb022beff019","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have gathered comprehensive information about the evolution system. Let me create a final summary report.\n\n## Summary: Population-Related Files in /workspace\n\nBased on my thorough search of the /workspace project, **there are NO files related to \"population\" in the traditional sense** (as in population-based optimization, genetic algorithms, or Pareto selection). However, I found an extensive **Self-Evolution System** that appears to be what you're looking for. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### Key Finding\n\nThe search for \"Population\", \"AddCandidate\", \"Promote\", \"Pareto\", \"fitness\", and \"EvaluateRun\" yielded no results. This indicates that the codebase does not implement population-based evolutionary algorithms. Instead, it implements a **self-improving system based on lessons and reflection**.\n\n### Evolution System Architecture\n\nThe Cloche project implements a sophisticated **self-evolution pipeline** designed to automatically improve workflows and prompts:\n\n**Files in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`:**\n\n1. **types.go** - Core data structures:\n   - `LLMClient` interface\n   - `CollectedData` - input to pipeline\n   - `Lesson` - structured insights with ID, category, insight, suggested_action, evidence, confidence\n   - `EvolutionResult` - pipeline output\n   - `Change` - tracks file modifications\n\n2. **orchestrator.go** - Main pipeline coordinator:\n   - Wires all stages together: Collector → Classifier → Reflector → Executor branches\n   - Handles lesson deduplication\n   - Routes lessons by category to appropriate executors\n   - Saves evolution results to store\n\n3. **collector.go** - Gathers workflow data:\n   - Collects runs, step executions, knowledge base, prompts, workflow file\n   - Scoped by project_dir + workflow_name\n\n4. **classifier.go** - LLM-based run categorization:\n   - Classifies runs as: bug, feedback, feature, enhancement, or chore\n\n5. **reflector.go** - LLM-based lesson extraction:\n   - Analyzes execution history and traces\n   - Produces structured lessons with evidence and confidence levels\n   - Filters by minimum confidence (low/medium/high)\n   - Deduplicates against knowledge base\n\n6. **curator.go** - Prompt evolution via ACE principles:\n   - Merges lessons into prompt files as structured bullets\n   - Guards against LLM conversational responses\n   - Post-write sanity checks with rollback capability\n   - Snapshot-based recovery\n\n7. **scriptgen.go** - Generates validation scripts:\n   - LLM-based script generation for new validation steps\n   - Path validation (scripts/ or .cloche/scripts/)\n   - Shebang line verification\n\n8. **trigger.go** - Evolution trigger mechanism:\n   - Debounces evolution runs per project+workflow\n   - Prevents duplicate analysis of rapid runs\n\n9. **audit.go** - Audit logging and state management:\n   - Records evolution passes as JSONL\n   - Manages snapshots for rollback\n   - Updates knowledge base with deduplication and pruning\n   - Supports MaxPromptBullets limit\n\n10. **llmclient.go** - CommandLLMClient implementation:\n    - Invokes external LLM via shell command\n    - Uses print mode (-p) for structured output\n    - Passes system prompt separately\n\n**Test files:**\n- `evolution_test.go` - Main evolution tests\n- `corruption_test.go` - Curator robustness tests (LLM output corruption scenarios)\n- `scriptgen_test.go` - Script generation tests\n- `trigger_test.go` - Debounce mechanism tests\n\n### Key Differences from Population-Based Evolution\n\nThis system uses:\n- **Structured lessons** (not candidate solutions)\n- **Confidence scoring** (high/medium/low, not fitness scores)\n- **ID-based deduplication** (not Pareto dominance)\n- **Lesson categories** (prompt_improvement, new_step - not genetic operators)\n- **Single best path** (not population selection)\n\n### Related Interfaces (in `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n```go\ntype EvolutionStore interface {\n    SaveEvolution(ctx context.Context, entry *EvolutionEntry) error\n    GetLastEvolution(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName string) (*EvolutionEntry, error)\n    ListRunsSince(ctx context.Context, projectDir, workflowName, sinceRunID string) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n}\n\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Design Documentation\n\n- **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-design.md`** - Complete architectural design\n- **`/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-24-self-evolution-implementation.md`** - Implementation tasks and plan\n\nThis is a **lesson-based evolution system**, not a population-based optimization system. It evolves workflows through accumulated knowledge from run history rather than maintaining candidate populations."}],"totalDurationMs":50825,"totalTokens":70247,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7353,"cache_read_input_tokens":61653,"output_tokens":1238,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7353},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
